<h1>About iCARE</h1>

<p>
    iCARE is a comprehensive healthcare management application designed by <strong>Group 12</strong>: Kene, Isaiah, Sydney, and Cooper. The project was built using the ASP.NET MVC Framework with a SQL Server database, <strong>Group12_iCAREDB</strong>.
</p>

<p>
    The application enables healthcare administrators and workers to manage patient data efficiently, ensuring a secure and organized environment for patient care. It includes features such as:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Managing patient records and medical history</li>
    <li>Role-based assignment of doctors and nurses to patients</li>
    <li>Document management for storing patient-related files and records</li>
</ul>

<p>
    This project was designed with the aim of providing an easy-to-use yet robust system for healthcare providers.
</p>

<h2>How to Run the Application</h2>
<p>
    <ol>
        <li>Download the database file (<strong>Group12_iCAREDB</strong>).</li>
        <li>Unblock the file by going to its properties.</li>
        <li>Restore the database in Microsoft SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS) and establish a connection.</li>
        <li>Open the project in Visual Studio (ASP.NET MVC).</li>
        <li>Ensure the configuration file is updated with your server name.</li>
    </ol>
</p>

<p>
    We have created all necessary models, controllers, and views required to run the application.
</p>

